<br>
Lots of players are dissatisfied with the &quot;cool&quot; factor of their character when raiding.  It's because raiding most of the time puts us (all of us, not just druids) in a single task mode where you have a prime purpose.  That role may change from raid to raid, but generally, for the duration of a raid you are expected to do the same thing.  <br>
<br>
I see everyone griping about their 50+ characters, regardless of class.  I guess it's just that the raiding scene sometimes lacks variety.  I also guess that our hands are tied in many cases because of game mechanics.  The latter is what people post on these boards about, but I don't think it's the whole picture.<br>
<br>
I know a couple druids (who also happen to post on these boards) named Seekr and Pobo that seem to really have fun druiding because they invent new ways to help the raid succeed (such as running out and helping the pullers, or organizing nuke groups, or blah blah blah).  In other words, they make themselves useful instead of following the same ol' routine.  If you get discouraged 50+, I'd suggest trying that. =)<br>
<br>
Re: the complaints on these boards tho...they are legitimate and warranted.  It sucks when you show up for a raid and can't do a single thing because of game mechanics (ie. heals that are too tiny, mobs that are too MR, debuffs that are too hard to land, buffs that nobody wants, etc). =p  But I still like playing. <p><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" BORDER="0"><TR BGCOLOR="#000000"><TD ALIGN="CENTER">
